<%# The ★ save + 🔔 notify cluster for the active filter, pinned to the right of
    the applied-filter chips. Logged-in users with an active filter only (an empty
    filter would be an "all events" firehose we don't offer).

    Deliberately ONE small isolated partial. The two-button model is on probation
    (★ = a silent saved interest, 🔔 = notifications layered on top): if it reads
    as two controls for the same thing, collapse it to a single button HERE —
    nothing in the model or the toggle_save/#notify lifecycle depends on there
    being two buttons.

    States (set from @notify_rule; see NotificationRulesController):
      • no rule           → ★ outline only. Tapping ★ saves a silent filter in
        place (toggle_save, enabled: false), re-rendering just this frame.
      • saved, notify off → ★ filled + 🔔 outline. Tapping 🔔 turns notifications
        on and opens the editor (#notify) to set the schedule/channels.
      • notifying          → ★ filled + 🔔 filled. ★ tap removes the saved filter
        entirely; 🔔 tap reopens the editor.

    Icon-only: the buttons ride the chip row's reserved height (padding gives the
    hit area, negative margin cancels the growth — see .notify-filter-link). The
    accessible name lives on aria-label. %>
<% if current_user.present? && @filter.active? %>
  <div class="filter-actions flex flex-row align-center">
    <%# ★ — toggle a silent saved filter in place; re-renders this frame only. %>
    <%= link_to toggle_save_notification_rules_path(q: @filter.queries, g: @filter.genres,
                  l: @filter.location_list, s: @filter.style_list, d: @filter.date_ranges),
          class: class_names('notify-filter-link', 'save-filter-link', active: @notify_rule.present?),
          'aria-label': t(@notify_rule ? 'events.index.save_filter_remove' : 'events.index.save_filter'),
          data: { turbo_method: :post, turbo_frame: 'filter-save' } do %>
      <% if @notify_rule %>
        <span class="star-fill" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      <% else %>
        <span class="ph ph-star" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      <% end %>
    <% end %>

    <%# 🔔 — only once saved. Turns notifications on and opens the editor; lit when
        the saved filter is actively notifying (enabled). %>
    <% if @notify_rule %>
      <%= link_to notify_notification_rule_path(@notify_rule),
            class: class_names('notify-filter-link', 'notify-bell-link', active: @notify_rule.enabled?),
            'aria-label': t(@notify_rule.enabled? ? 'events.index.notify_filter_existing' : 'events.index.notify_filter'),
            data: { turbo_method: :post, turbo_frame: '_top' } do %>
        <% if @notify_rule.enabled? %>
          <span class="notify-bell-fill" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <% else %>
          <span class="ph ph-bell" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <% end %>
      <% end %>
    <% end %>
  </div>
<% end %>
